Description: Another weekend of friends crushing their races. Very easy to get inspired by everyone 🙌 Switched it up today to see something a bit different.
Warm up with the crew, then solo for a bit of something resembling a workout. Post run grub and sendoff for Ailsa, setting off for warmer weather. See ya in Phoenix soon 👋
Snow in the eyes, welcome back (I should really get clear glasses for winter).
Easy miles with Kevin and Keenan to round out the week. Hamstring/knee reminding me it's still there, thanks guys. Biggest mileage week in awhile though!
Party lap with Tyler Williams as he crushes the Everest Challenge 👏
Montane, Horseshoe, plus a bit. Easy, solid fuelling session. Time to start training the gut. Warmup with Nic, then solo for the rest. Nate flyby 👋

Full on fight class on the east side across the whole path. Made sure not to be kicked in the face by the guy practicing high kicks. Wasn't going to be the one to tell them they were in the way 😂 Easy with hill strides, they were feeling a bit better today. Progress 👊
Good miles planned for the week, keeping it all easy.
Where you question everything in life 😂 Holy blizzard. Treadmill next time! Good grinding out there with Keenan though.

Good accumulation overnight for some unplowed pathway running this morning. Easy miles w/ Keenan. Working all the muscles these past few days. Classic winter running in snow. Definitely feeling it 😮‍💨
Some ice, some snow, some dry path. Then the squall rolled in 🌨️, covered everything with a good dusting.  Attempted workout, did what I could.

Ya it's here (hooray?). Operation find a hill that isn't ice/snow for hill strides was in effect. All the usual spots were covered. Used a bit of the 10th Street hill, fortunate the shoulder had somewhat melted. Variable conditions on the pathways as well. Thinking west would have been better than east today.
Hip still not happy outside. To the TM.
Uphill treadmill for this beat up body. Seeing if some warmth can right this ship 👊
Four Dogs, Cabin, 88, Evil w/ the boys. Another successful one! Portland Street Pizza though 🤌
Late edition, good catch up with friends. Glenmore pathway has seen better days, good for an easy cruise but lots and lots of ice! Nice to change it up one last time before the Bow days of winter.
Cautiously optimistic? Hopeful. Easy miles to see where we're at. Keenan flyby, shared some miles. Loving the pathway conditions. Missed that whole chinook, terrible timing for some days off!
Had to take some days off, body was continuing to rebel. Hopefully on the right track now 🤞 Lil treadmill action post photoshoot at Nose w/ Dylan & Braden.

Solid Saturday w/ Keenan. Still keeping it easy but nice to have a longer session on the legs again. Hopefully some intensity next week 🤞 Healthy looking yote on the path in the park, magpies were keeping an eye on him. Liyang flyby too 🔥 👋
Always nice getting out in the sun during these short winter days.
Scott flyby, Matt flyby 👋 (Not feeling so hot today what the heck! Tomorrow will be better 🤞)
Optimistic, let's see if we can get this build rolling again. Bonus gut training, learning from the best 👊

Description: Throughout my career I’ve been on both ends of this spectrum and have recently found what I consider to be a great balance between athlete and personal life. But I’ve noticed more and more how many people flip this and go “all in” leave no stone unturned and make their training the #1 priority in life. I don’t think this is entirely the best way to live or even feasible for most, but man it can be toxic as a professional athlete to compete with. Dog Miles- 880.97

Strange name, but she tortoise well.
